<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="111" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="36.[831,1437,1426,1675]" pageId="36" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[831,965,1426,1449]" pageId="36" pageNumber="111">Comments:</emphasis>
The species was redescribed and its aedeagus illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation author="Lobl I." box="[1099,1226,1459,1482]" pageId="36" pageNumber="111" pagination="937 - 1006" refId="ref30904" refString="Lobl I. 1971. Scaphidiidae von Ceylon (Coleoptera). Revue suisse de Zoologie 78: 937 - 1006." type="journal article" year="1971">Löbl, 1971</bibRefCitation>
. The female from Batudulang has a reddish anterior part of the elytron clearly separated from yellowish elytral apex by a dark transverse band, as other specimens coming from different areas. The 
<specimenCount box="[997,1107,1588,1611]" pageId="36" pageNumber="111" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
from Batudulang differ by the elytra uniformly dark from their bases upto the yellowish apical bands.
</paragraph>
